{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841661695,"sessionID":"ses_287971590ffeHr5qKGy0e8hRpu","part":{"id":"prt_d786934a4001ZuBsy00e7pyEZu","messageID":"msg_d7869225b001ajRQo3PHV2vNVM","sessionID":"ses_287971590ffeHr5qKGy0e8hRpu","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-0096fb323c07401c9b8fa9da85979b29","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-004/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-004/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架 Proposal\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: 为 WorkloadManager 构建 HTTP 服务框架，作为 agentcube 核心服务器的网络层基础，提供:\n6: \n7: 1. **RESTful API 基础设施**: 支持 Sandbox、SandboxClaim、Session 等资源的 CRUD 操作\n8: 2. **中间件架构**: 提供请求日志、认证、限流、CORS 等可插拔能力\n9: 3. **生命周期管理**: 优雅启动、信号处理、连接清理\n10: 4. **可观测性**: 健康检查、就绪探针、Prometheus 指标端点\n11: 5. **错误处理**: 统一的错误响应格式与日志记录\n12: \n13: ## Scope\n14: \n15: ### In Scope\n16: \n17: | Deliverable | Description |\n18: |-------------|-------------|\n19: | `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` | HTTP 服务器核心实现，包括启动、关闭、配置 |\n20: | `pkg/workloadmanager/router.go` | 路由初始化与路由组管理 |\n21: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/base.go` | 基础 Handler 接口定义 |\n22: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health.go` | 健康检查与就绪探针实现 |\n23: | `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/logging.go` | 请求日志中间件 |\n24: | `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/recovery.go` | Panic 恢复中间件 |\n25: | `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/cors.go` | CORS 中间件（可选） |\n26: | `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` | 请求/响应数据结构定义 |\n27: \n28: ### API Endpoints Framework\n29: \n30: ```\n31: /api/v1/\n32: ├── healthz          — 健康检查 (GET)\n33: ├── readyz           — 就绪探针 (GET)\n34: ├── sandboxes        — Sandbox CRUD (待后续 AR 实现)\n35: ├── sandboxclaims    — SandboxClaim CRUD (待后续 AR 实现)\n36: └── sessions         — Session 管理 (待后续 AR 实现)\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ### Out of Scope\n40: \n41: - 业务 Handler 实现（Sandbox、SandboxClaim、Session）\n42: - WebSocket 路由与连接管理\n43: - 认证授权逻辑\n44: - 具体的限流策略实现\n45: - 数据库/存储层集成\n46: \n47: ## Impact Analysis\n48: \n49: ### Upstream Dependencies\n50: \n51: | Dependency | Impact |\n52: |------------|--------|\n53: | Go 标准库 `net/http` | 核心依赖 |\n54: | 可能的第三方路由库（如 chi, gorilla/mux） | 待设计决策，可选 |\n55: \n56: ### Downstream Consumers\n57: \n58: | Consumer | Usage |\n59: |----------|-------|\n60: | WorkloadManager 业务逻辑 | 通过 Handler 接口注册业务逻辑 |\n61: | 监控系统 | 通过 `/metrics` 端点采集指标 |\n62: | Kubernetes 探针 | 通过 `/healthz`, `/readyz` 检查服务状态 |\n63: | 客户端应用 | 通过 RESTful API 访问服务 |\n64: \n65: ### Breaking Change Considerations\n66: \n67: - **路由路径变更**: API 路径设计影响所有客户端\n68: - **错误格式变更**: 统一错误响应格式影响客户端错误处理逻辑\n69: - **中间件顺序**: 中间件执行顺序可能影响请求处理流程\n70: \n71: ## Alternatives Considered\n72: \n73: ### Alternative 1: 使用标准库 net/http\n74: \n75: **Approach**: 仅使用 `net/http` 标准库，手动实现路由与中间件。\n76: \n77: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n78: |--------|------------|\n79: | Pros | 无外部依赖；完全控制；性能最优 |\n80: | Cons | 路由功能有限；需要手动实现中间件链；缺乏社区生态 |\n81: \n82: **Decision**: 待评估。对于简单场景可行，但路由分组、路径参数等功能需要额外实现。\n83: \n84: ### Alternative 2: 使用 gorilla/mux\n85: \n86: **Approach**: 使用成熟的 `gorilla/mux` 路由库。\n87: \n88: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n89: |--------|------------|\n90: | Pros | 功能完善；社区活跃；中间件支持好 |\n91: | Cons | 外部依赖；性能略逊于 chi |\n92: \n93: **Decision**: 可选方案。\n94: \n95: ### Alternative 3: 使用 chi 路由器\n96: \n97: **Approach**: 使用轻量级 `chi` 路由器。\n98: \n99: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n100: |--------|------------|\n101: | Pros | 零依赖；性能优秀；兼容 net/http；内置中间件 |\n102: | Cons | 社区规模小于 gorilla/mux |\n103: \n104: **Decision**: 推荐。chi 轻量且符合 Go 惯例。\n105: \n106: ### Alternative 4: 使用 Gin/Echo 框架\n107: \n108: **Approach**: 使用完整 Web 框架（Gin 或 Echo）。\n109: \n110: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n111: |--------|------------|\n112: | Pros | 功能全面；性能优秀；生态丰富 |\n113: | Cons | 过度封装；违反 AgentCube 渐进式设计原则 |\n114: \n115: **Decision**: 拒绝。AgentCube 倾向于使用标准库 + 轻量级工具，而非重型框架。\n116: \n117: ## Risks\n118: \n119: | Risk | Mitigation |\n120: |------|------------|\n121: | 路由库选型错误 | 设计阶段充分评估 chi/gorilla/mux/stdlib，保留切换能力 |\n122: | 中间件顺序导致 Bug | 明确中间件执行顺序文档，添加集成测试 |\n123: | 错误响应格式不统一 | 定义 Error 结构体，所有 Handler 使用统一错误返回方法 |\n124: | 性能瓶颈 | 基准测试关键端点，监控 p99 延迟 |\n125: \n126: ## Implementation Notes\n127: \n128: 1. **配置**: 使用环境变量或配置文件指定端口、超时等参数\n129: 2. **日志**: 集成 pkg/logging，记录请求 ID、路径、状态码、延迟\n130: 3. **优雅关闭**: 监听 SIGTERM/SIGINT，等待现有连接完成（最长 30s）\n131: 4. **健康检查**: `/healthz` 总是返回 200，`/readyz` 检查依赖服务状态\n132: 5. **中间件模式**: 使用 Go 标准中间件签名 `func(http.Handler) http.Handler`\n133: \n134: ## References\n135: \n136: - Go net/http: https://pkg.go.dev/net/http\n137: - chi router: https://github.com/go-chi/chi\n138: - Kubernetes Healthz Pattern: https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/configure-pod-container/configure-liveness-readiness-probes/\n\n(End of file - total 138 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架 Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\n为 WorkloadManager 构建 HTTP 服务框架，作为 agentcube 核心服务器的网络层基础，提供:\n\n1. **RESTful API 基础设施**: 支持 Sandbox、SandboxClaim、Session 等资源的 CRUD 操作\n2. **中间件架构**: 提供请求日志、认证、限流、CORS 等可插拔能力\n3. **生命周期管理**: 优雅启动、信号处理、连接清理\n4. **可观测性**: 健康检查、就绪探针、Prometheus 指标端点\n5. **错误处理**: 统一的错误响应格式与日志记录\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` | HTTP 服务器核心实现，包括启动、关闭、配置 |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/router.go` | 路由初始化与路由组管理 |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-004/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775841661672,"end":1775841661693}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841661697,"sessionID":"ses_287971590ffeHr5qKGy0e8hRpu","part":{"id":"prt_d7869465c001tAwj4HgMS6M8of","messageID":"msg_d7869225b001ajRQo3PHV2vNVM","sessionID":"ses_287971590ffeHr5qKGy0e8hRpu","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-041024088cfe456084cb2205abaec53b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-003/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-003/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-003 — CRD 共享类型与常量 Proposal\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define shared types, constants, and common utilities for CRD type definitions in the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` package. These shared elements provide:\n6: \n7: 1. **Common Type Definitions**: Shared structs used across multiple CRDs (TargetPort, ProtocolType, AuthModeType)\n8: 2. **Label/Annotation Constants**: Standard labels and annotations for sandbox resources\n9: 3. **Condition Types**: Standard condition type constants for status reporting\n10: 4. **Validation Helpers**: Shared validation constants and patterns\n11: \n12: ## Scope\n13: \n14: ### In Scope\n15: \n16: | Deliverable | Description |\n17: |-------------|-------------|\n18: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` | Shared type definitions (TargetPort, ProtocolType, AuthModeType) |\n19: | Label/Annotation constants | Standard labels/annotations for sandbox lifecycle |\n20: | Condition type constants | Standard condition types for status reporting |\n21: | Default value constants | Default timeout/duration constants |\n22: \n23: ### Type Definitions Required\n24: \n25: #### Shared Types (Already Defined)\n26: \n27: - `TargetPort`: Port configuration with pathPrefix, name, port, protocol\n28: - `ProtocolType`: Enum for HTTP/HTTPS\n29: - `AuthModeType`: Enum for picod/none\n30: \n31: #### Constants to Define\n32: \n33: - **Label Constants**: Sandbox owner labels, runtime type labels\n34: - **Annotation Constants**: Session tracking, authentication annotations\n35: - **Condition Types**: Ready, Available, Progressing, Degraded\n36: - **Default Values**: Session timeout, max session duration defaults\n37: \n38: ### Out of Scope\n39: \n40: - Controller implementation (`pkg/controllers/`)\n41: - Webhook validation logic\n42: - CRD YAML generation (handled by `make gen-crd`)\n43: - client-go code generation (handled by `make gen-client`)\n44: - AgentRuntime CRD (AR-001)\n45: - CodeInterpreter CRD (AR-002)\n46: \n47: ## Impact Analysis\n48: \n49: ### Upstream Dependencies\n50: \n51: | Dependency | Impact |\n52: |------------|--------|\n53: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | Required for metav1.Condition type constants |\n54: \n55: ### Downstream Consumers\n56: \n57: | Consumer | Usage |\n58: |----------|-------|\n59: | AR-001 AgentRuntime | Uses TargetPort, ProtocolType |\n60: | AR-002 CodeInterpreter | Uses TargetPort, ProtocolType, AuthModeType |\n61: | Workload Manager | Uses label/annotation constants |\n62: | Router | Uses condition type constants for status checks |\n63: \n64: ## Alternatives Considered\n65: \n66: | Alternative | Pros | Cons | Decision |\n67: |-------------|------|------|----------|\n68: | **Inline constants per CRD** | Localized definition | Duplication, inconsistency | Rejected |\n69: | **Separate constants package** | Decoupled constants | Import complexity | Rejected - keep in shared_types.go |\n70: | **Generated constants** | Automated consistency | Over-engineering for S-size | Rejected |\n71: \n72: ## Risks\n73: \n74: | Risk | Mitigation |\n75: |------|------------|\n76: | Constant naming conflicts | Use package prefix pattern |\n77: | Breaking constant changes | Document stability expectations |\n78: | Condition type proliferation | Define minimal set initially |\n79: \n80: ## Implementation Notes\n81: \n82: 1. **Naming Convention**: Use `LabelKey*`, `AnnotationKey*`, `ConditionType*` patterns\n83: 2. **Documentation**: Add godoc comments for all constants\n84: 3. **Location**: All constants in `shared_types.go` for easy discovery\n85: 4. **Stability**: Mark constants with stability expectations\n86: \n87: ## References\n88: \n89: - Kubernetes API Conventions: https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md\n90: - Kubebuilder Book: https://book.kubebuilder.io/\n91: - AR-001 Design: `changes/AR-001/design.md`\n92: - AR-002 Design: `changes/AR-002/design.md`\n\n(End of file - total 92 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-003 — CRD 共享类型与常量 Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine shared types, constants, and common utilities for CRD type definitions in the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` package. These shared elements provide:\n\n1. **Common Type Definitions**: Shared structs used across multiple CRDs (TargetPort, ProtocolType, AuthModeType)\n2. **Label/Annotation Constants**: Standard labels and annotations for sandbox resources\n3. **Condition Types**: Standard condition type constants for status reporting\n4. **Validation Helpers**: Shared validation constants and patterns\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` | Shared type definitions (TargetPort, ProtocolType, AuthModeType) |\n| Label/Annotation constants | Standard labels/annotations for sandbox lifecycle |\n| Condition type constants | Standard condition types for status reporting |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-003/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775841661675,"end":1775841661696}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841661699,"sessionID":"ses_287971590ffeHr5qKGy0e8hRpu","part":{"id":"prt_d786949fe001l3PRHEbr206FMC","messageID":"msg_d7869225b001ajRQo3PHV2vNVM","sessionID":"ses_287971590ffeHr5qKGy0e8hRpu","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-d110ada41f164eb682557c5749fceae0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-001/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-001/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义 Proposal\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define the foundational Go type structures for `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` CRDs in the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` package. These types serve as the core data model for AgentCube's sandbox orchestration platform, enabling:\n6: \n7: 1. **Sandbox Template Definition**: Users define pod templates and runtime parameters via CRDs\n8: 2. **Controller Integration**: The workload manager controller uses these types to create/manage `Sandbox` and `SandboxClaim` resources\n9: 3. **Client Generation**: These types are the source for `k8s.io/code-generator` to produce typed clients, informers, and listers (see `deployment/client-go.md`)\n10: 4. **Helm Chart CRDs**: `controller-gen` generates CRD YAML from these types (see `manifests/charts/base/crds/`)\n11: \n12: ## Scope\n13: \n14: ### In Scope\n15: \n16: | Deliverable | Description |\n17: |-------------|-------------|\n18: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go` | Type definitions for AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, TargetPort, and related structs |\n19: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Package documentation with boilerplate |\n20: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` | Scheme registration for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` |\n21: \n22: ### Type Definitions Required\n23: \n24: #### AgentRuntime\n25: \n26: ```\n27: AgentRuntime\n28: ├── Spec\n29: │   ├── Ports ([]TargetPort, JSON: targetPort)\n30: │   ├── Template (*SandboxTemplate, JSON: podTemplate, required)\n31: │   ├── SessionTimeout (*metav1.Duration, JSON: sessionTimeout, default: 15m)\n32: │   └── MaxSessionDuration (*metav1.Duration, JSON: maxSessionDuration, default: 8h)\n33: ├── Status\n34: │   └── Conditions ([]metav1.Condition, optional)\n35: └── List: AgentRuntimeList\n36: ```\n37: \n38: #### CodeInterpreter\n39: \n40: ```\n41: CodeInterpreter\n42: ├── Spec\n43: │   ├── Ports ([]TargetPort, JSON: ports)\n44: │   ├── Template (*CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate, JSON: template, required)\n45: │   ├── SessionTimeout (*metav1.Duration, default: 15m)\n46: │   ├── MaxSessionDuration (*metav1.Duration, default: 8h)\n47: │   ├── WarmPoolSize (*int32)\n48: │   └── AuthMode (AuthModeType, default: picod, enum: picod|none)\n49: ├── Status\n50: │   ├── Conditions ([]metav1.Condition)\n51: │   └── Ready (*bool)\n52: └── List: CodeInterpreterList\n53: ```\n54: \n55: #### Supporting Types\n56: \n57: - `TargetPort`: Port configuration with optional pathPrefix/name, required port (uint32), protocol (HTTP|HTTPS)\n58: - `ProtocolType`: Enum for HTTP/HTTPS\n59: - `AuthModeType`: Enum for picod/none\n60: - `SandboxTemplate`: Labels, annotations, and embedded `corev1.PodSpec`\n61: - `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`: Image, command, args, env, resources, runtimeClassName, etc.\n62: \n63: ### Out of Scope\n64: \n65: - Controller implementation (`pkg/controllers/`)\n66: - Webhook validation logic\n67: - CRD YAML generation (handled by `make gen-crd`)\n68: - client-go code generation (handled by `make gen-client`)\n69: - HTTP API handlers (`pkg/api/`)\n70: \n71: ## Impact Analysis\n72: \n73: ### Upstream Dependencies\n74: \n75: | Dependency | Impact |\n76: |------------|--------|\n77: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | Required for metav1.ObjectMeta, metav1.Duration, metav1.Condition |\n78: | `k8s.io/api/corev1` | Required for embedded PodSpec in templates |\n79: \n80: ### Downstream Consumers\n81: \n82: | Consumer | Usage |\n83: |----------|-------|\n84: | `make gen-crd` | Generates CRD YAML to `manifests/charts/base/crds/` |\n85: | `make gen-client` | Generates typed clients, informers, listers to `client-go/` |\n86: | Workload Manager (`cmd/workload-manager`) | Reads CRD specs to create Sandbox/SandboxClaim |\n87: | Router (`cmd/router`) | May reference CRD types for routing logic |\n88: | E2E Tests | Validates CRD creation and behavior |\n89: | Helm Chart | Ships generated CRD YAML for installation |\n90: \n91: ### Breaking Change Considerations\n92: \n93: - **Version Stability**: Using `v1alpha1` signals API instability; changes may break existing workloads\n94: - **Field Defaults**: Kubebuilder markers set defaults at CRD level; changing defaults affects existing unlabeled resources\n95: - **Enum Values**: Adding/removing enum values (ProtocolType, AuthModeType) requires CRD schema update\n96: \n97: ## Alternatives Considered\n98: \n99: ### Alternative 1: Use Unstructured CRDs\n100: \n101: **Approach**: Define CRDs via raw YAML without Go types, consume via `dynamic.Client`.\n102: \n103: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n104: |--------|------------|\n105: | Pros | No code generation dependency; faster initial setup |\n106: | Cons | No type safety; no informer/lister generation; harder validation; no IDE support |\n107: \n108: **Decision**: Rejected. AgentCube requires typed clients for controller-runtime integration and test reliability.\n109: \n110: ### Alternative 2: Single Unified CRD\n111: \n112: **Approach**: Merge AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter into one CRD with a `type` discriminator field.\n113: \n114: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n115: |--------|------------|\n116: | Pros | Fewer CRDs; simpler client-go generation |\n117: | Cons | Schema complexity; divergent status fields (`ready` only for CodeInterpreter); authMode only applies to CodeInterpreter; warmPoolSize only for CodeInterpreter |\n118: \n119: **Decision**: Rejected. The two CRDs serve distinct use cases with sufficiently different spec structures.\n120: \n121: ### Alternative 3: External Template Reference\n122: \n123: **Approach**: Use `TemplateRef` (name/namespace) instead of embedded template.\n124: \n125: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n126: |--------|------------|\n127: | Pros | Reusable templates; smaller CRD instances |\n128: | Cons | Additional lookup step; template lifecycle complexity; no inline customization |\n129: \n130: **Decision**: Rejected for initial implementation. Inline templates match agent-sandbox conventions and simplify the user experience. May consider as future extension.\n131: \n132: ### Alternative 4: Duration as int64 seconds\n133: \n134: **Approach**: Use `int64` for timeout/duration fields instead of `metav1.Duration`.\n135: \n136: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n137: |--------|------------|\n138: | Pros | Simpler serialization; no string parsing |\n139: | Cons | Non-standard K8s API; human readability reduced (e.g., \"8h\" vs 28800) |\n140: \n141: **Decision**: Rejected. `metav1.Duration` follows Kubernetes API conventions and provides human-readable defaults (\"15m\", \"8h\").\n142: \n143: ## Risks\n144: \n145: | Risk | Mitigation |\n146: |------|------------|\n147: | Kubebuilder marker typos | Run `make gen-crd` and verify output YAML |\n148: | Missing JSON tags | Use `golangci-lint` with tag-related rules |\n149: | PodSpec embedding complexity | Follow `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` patterns |\n150: | Code-generator version mismatch | Pin `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1 per `hack/update-codegen.sh` |\n151: \n152: ## Implementation Notes\n153: \n154: 1. **Boilerplate**: Use `hack/boilerplate.go.txt` header via `make gen-copyright`\n155: 2. **JSON Tags**: camelCase per project conventions (e.g., `targetPort`, `podTemplate`, `sessionTimeout`)\n156: 3. **Kubebuilder Markers**: Apply `+kubebuilder:object:root`, `+kubebuilder:subresource:status`, `+kubebuilder:default`, `+kubebuilder:validation:Required`, `+kubebuilder:validation:Enum`\n157: 4. **Printer Columns**: Add `+kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"` for `Age` column\n158: \n159: ## References\n160: \n161: - Kubernetes API Conventions: https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md\n162: - Kubebuilder Book: https://book.kubebuilder.io/\n163: - agent-sandbox API: https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox\n164: - Spec: `changes/AR-001/spec.md`\n165: - Client-go reference: `deployment/client-go.md`\n\n(End of file - total 165 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义 Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the foundational Go type structures for `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` CRDs in the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` package. These types serve as the core data model for AgentCube's sandbox orchestration platform, enabling:\n\n1. **Sandbox Template Definition**: Users define pod templates and runtime parameters via CRDs\n2. **Controller Integration**: The workload manager controller uses these types to create/manage `Sandbox` and `SandboxClaim` resources\n3. **Client Generation**: These types are the source for `k8s.io/code-generator` to produce typed clients, informers, and listers (see `deployment/client-go.md`)\n4. **Helm Chart CRDs**: `controller-gen` generates CRD YAML from these types (see `manifests/charts/base/crds/`)\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go` | Type definitions for AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, TargetPort, and related structs |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Package documentation with boilerplate |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` | Scheme registration for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-001/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775841661677,"end":1775841661697}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841661714,"sessionID":"ses_287971590ffeHr5qKGy0e8hRpu","part":{"id":"prt_d78694e79001032sbL5IGm0ytv","messageID":"msg_d7869225b001ajRQo3PHV2vNVM","sessionID":"ses_287971590ffeHr5qKGy0e8hRpu","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-12930811c0eb413985b15cd84edd6066","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package v1alpha1\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n5: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n6: )\n7: \n8: // AgentRuntime is the Schema for the agentruntimes API.\n9: // It represents a runtime configuration for an AI agent sandbox,\n10: // including pod templates, session timeouts, and network port configurations.\n11: //\n12: // +genclient\n13: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n14: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n15: // +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n16: // +kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced\n17: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"\n18: type AgentRuntime struct {\n19: \tmetav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n20: \tmetav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n21: \n22: \tSpec   AgentRuntimeSpec   `json:\"spec\"`\n23: \tStatus AgentRuntimeStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n24: }\n25: \n26: // AgentRuntimeSpec defines the desired state of AgentRuntime.\n27: type AgentRuntimeSpec struct {\n28: \t// Ports specifies the network ports to expose from the sandbox.\n29: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n30: \t// +listType=atomic\n31: \tPorts []TargetPort `json:\"targetPort\"`\n32: \n33: \t// Template defines the pod template for the sandbox.\n34: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n35: \tTemplate *SandboxTemplate `json:\"podTemplate\" protobuf:\"bytes,1,opt,name=podTemplate\"`\n36: \n37: \t// SessionTimeout specifies the idle timeout for a session.\n38: \t// Default is 15 minutes.\n39: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n40: \t// +kubebuilder:default=\"15m\"\n41: \tSessionTimeout *metav1.Duration `json:\"sessionTimeout,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,2,opt,name=sessionTimeout\"`\n42: \n43: \t// MaxSessionDuration specifies the maximum duration a session can exist.\n44: \t// Default is 8 hours.\n45: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n46: \t// +kubebuilder:default=\"8h\"\n47: \tMaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration `json:\"maxSessionDuration,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,3,opt,name=maxSessionDuration\"`\n48: }\n49: \n50: // AgentRuntimeStatus defines the observed state of AgentRuntime.\n51: type AgentRuntimeStatus struct {\n52: \t// Conditions represents the latest available observations of the AgentRuntime's state.\n53: \t// +optional\n54: \t// +listType=atomic\n55: \tConditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n56: }\n57: \n58: // SandboxTemplate defines the pod template for creating sandbox pods.\n59: type SandboxTemplate struct {\n60: \t// Labels are applied to the sandbox pod.\n61: \t// +optional\n62: \tLabels map[string]string `json:\"labels,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,1,rep,name=labels\"`\n63: \n64: \t// Annotations are applied to the sandbox pod.\n65: \t// +optional\n66: \tAnnotations map[string]string `json:\"annotations,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,2,rep,name=annotations\"`\n67: \n68: \t// Spec is the PodSpec for the sandbox pod.\n69: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n70: \tSpec corev1.PodSpec `json:\"spec\" protobuf:\"bytes,3,opt,name=spec\"`\n71: }\n72: \n73: // AgentRuntimeList contains a list of AgentRuntime resources.\n74: //\n75: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n76: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n77: type AgentRuntimeList struct {\n78: \tmetav1.TypeMeta `json:\",inline\"`\n79: \tmetav1.ListMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n80: \n81: \tItems []AgentRuntime `json:\"items\"`\n82: }\n\n(End of file - total 82 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package v1alpha1\n\nimport (\n\tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n\tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n)\n\n// AgentRuntime is the Schema for the agentruntimes API.\n// It represents a runtime configuration for an AI agent sandbox,\n// including pod templates, session timeouts, and network port configurations.\n//\n// +genclient\n// +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n// +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n// +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n// +kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced\n// +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"\ntype AgentRuntime struct {\n\tmetav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n\tmetav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go","time":{"start":1775841661679,"end":1775841661713}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841661736,"sessionID":"ses_287971590ffeHr5qKGy0e8hRpu","part":{"id":"prt_d786952c2001FV8KZtD9IaRyxW","messageID":"msg_d7869225b001ajRQo3PHV2vNVM","sessionID":"ses_287971590ffeHr5qKGy0e8hRpu","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-fe75806aba0d4289a6564286a1087eea","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package v1alpha1\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n5: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n6: )\n7: \n8: // CodeInterpreter is the Schema for the codeinterpreters API.\n9: // It represents a specialized runtime for code execution environments\n10: // with additional features like warm pool management and authentication modes.\n11: //\n12: // +genclient\n13: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n14: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n15: // +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n16: // +kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced\n17: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"\n18: type CodeInterpreter struct {\n19: \tmetav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n20: \tmetav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n21: \n22: \tSpec   CodeInterpreterSpec   `json:\"spec\"`\n23: \tStatus CodeInterpreterStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n24: }\n25: \n26: // CodeInterpreterSpec defines the desired state of CodeInterpreter.\n27: type CodeInterpreterSpec struct {\n28: \t// Ports specifies the network ports to expose from the code interpreter.\n29: \t// +optional\n30: \t// +listType=atomic\n31: \tPorts []TargetPort `json:\"ports,omitempty\"`\n32: \n33: \t// Template defines the sandbox template for the code interpreter.\n34: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n35: \tTemplate *CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate `json:\"template\"`\n36: \n37: \t// SessionTimeout specifies the idle timeout for a session.\n38: \t// Default is 15 minutes.\n39: \t// +kubebuilder:default=\"15m\"\n40: \tSessionTimeout *metav1.Duration `json:\"sessionTimeout,omitempty\"`\n41: \n42: \t// MaxSessionDuration specifies the maximum duration a session can exist.\n43: \t// Default is 8 hours.\n44: \t// +kubebuilder:default=\"8h\"\n45: \tMaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration `json:\"maxSessionDuration,omitempty\"`\n46: \n47: \t// WarmPoolSize specifies the number of pre-warmed instances to maintain.\n48: \t// +optional\n49: \tWarmPoolSize *int32 `json:\"warmPoolSize,omitempty\"`\n50: \n51: \t// AuthMode specifies the authentication mode for the code interpreter.\n52: \t// Default is \"picod\".\n53: \t// +kubebuilder:default=picod\n54: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=picod;none\n55: \t// +optional\n56: \tAuthMode AuthModeType `json:\"authMode,omitempty\"`\n57: }\n58: \n59: // CodeInterpreterStatus defines the observed state of CodeInterpreter.\n60: type CodeInterpreterStatus struct {\n61: \t// Conditions represents the latest available observations of the CodeInterpreter's state.\n62: \t// +optional\n63: \t// +listType=atomic\n64: \tConditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n65: \n66: \t// Ready indicates whether the CodeInterpreter is ready to serve requests.\n67: \t// +optional\n68: \tReady bool `json:\"ready,omitempty\"`\n69: }\n70: \n71: // CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate defines the sandbox template for code interpreter pods.\n72: type CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate struct {\n73: \t// Labels are applied to the code interpreter pod.\n74: \t// +optional\n75: \tLabels map[string]string `json:\"labels,omitempty\"`\n76: \n77: \t// Annotations are applied to the code interpreter pod.\n78: \t// +optional\n79: \tAnnotations map[string]string `json:\"annotations,omitempty\"`\n80: \n81: \t// RuntimeClassName is the name of the runtime class to use for the pod.\n82: \t// +optional\n83: \tRuntimeClassName *string `json:\"runtimeClassName,omitempty\"`\n84: \n85: \t// Image specifies the container image for the code interpreter.\n86: \tImage string `json:\"image,omitempty\"`\n87: \n88: \t// ImagePullPolicy specifies the image pull policy.\n89: \t// +optional\n90: \tImagePullPolicy corev1.PullPolicy `json:\"imagePullPolicy,omitempty\"`\n91: \n92: \t// ImagePullSecrets specifies the secrets for pulling the container image.\n93: \t// +optional\n94: \t// +patchMergeKey=name\n95: \t// +patchStrategy=merge\n96: \t// +listType=map\n97: \t// +listMapKey=name\n98: \tImagePullSecrets []corev1.LocalObjectReference `json:\"imagePullSecrets,omitempty\"`\n99: \n100: \t// Environment specifies environment variables for the container.\n101: \t// +optional\n102: \t// +listType=atomic\n103: \tEnvironment []corev1.EnvVar `json:\"environment,omitempty\"`\n104: \n105: \t// Command specifies the container command.\n106: \t// +optional\n107: \t// +listType=atomic\n108: \tCommand []string `json:\"command,omitempty\"`\n109: \n110: \t// Args specifies the container arguments.\n111: \t// +optional\n112: \t// +listType=atomic\n113: \tArgs []string `json:\"args,omitempty\"`\n114: \n115: \t// Resources specifies the compute resources for the container.\n116: \t// +optional\n117: \tResources corev1.ResourceRequirements `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n118: }\n119: \n120: // CodeInterpreterList contains a list of CodeInterpreter resources.\n121: //\n122: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n123: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n124: type CodeInterpreterList struct {\n125: \tmetav1.TypeMeta `json:\",inline\"`\n126: \tmetav1.ListMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n127: \n128: \tItems []CodeInterpreter `json:\"items\"`\n129: }\n\n(End of file - total 129 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package v1alpha1\n\nimport (\n\t